<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078>
    bibo:endPage "49" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" ;
    bibo:startPage "35" ;
    bibo:volume "67" ;
    dc:creator "Jia, Fenglong; Liang, Zulong; Fikacek, Martin" ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "A review of Himalcercyon stat. nov., with description of a new species from the Chinese Himalaya and an updated key to Asian genera of Megasternini (Coleoptera, Hydrophilidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure1>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure2>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure4>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure5>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure8>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure6>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure7>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure3> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Habitus and genital morphology of Himalcercyon species. A-D. H. mirus (A, B. Paratypes; C, D. Holotype). E-H. H. franzi sp. nov. (E, F. Paratypes; G, H. Holotype). A, E. Dorsal view; B, F. Lateral view; C, G. Aedeagus in dorsal view; D, H. Sternite IX in dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/408727" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Morphology of Himalcercyon mirus (Hebauer, 2002). A. Complete ventral view. B. Mentum. C. Prosternal carina in ventrolateral view. D. Prosternum and hypomeron. E. Meso- and metaventrite. F. Details of mesoventral plate." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/408728" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Known distribution of Himalcercyon: Circles. H. mirus (Hebauer); Square. H. franzi sp. nov. Color shading of the map indicated altitude: green = lowest, brown = highest." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/408730" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure5>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Ventral view of thorax of eastern Palaearctic and Oriental genera of the Megasternini. A. Cryptopleurum ferrugineum. B. Megasternum concinnum. C. Pacrillum manchuricum. D. Pachysternum nigrovittatum. E. Peltocercyon coomani. F. Armostus schenklingi." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/408731" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure8>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Ventral view of thorax and additional diagnostic characters of eastern Palaearctic and Oriental genera of the Megasternini. A-C. Ventral view: A. Pseudocercyon andrewesi. B. Cercyon sp. C. Gillisius madurensis, holotype. D-H. Other characters: D. Cryptopleurum coomani, mentum. E. Emmidolium excavatum, pronotum. F. Bolbonotum sp., base of elytra. G. Kahanga inconspicua, holotype, base of elytra. H. Australocyon sp. (A. pilocnemoides group), hind femur." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/408734" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Ventral view of thorax of eastern Palaearctic and Oriental genera of the Megasternini. A. Morastus gracilipalpis. B. Oosternum sp. (O. soricoides group). C. Emmidolium excavatum. D. Chimaerocyon shimadai. E. Paroosternum sp. F. Oreosternum frigidum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/408732" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure7>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Ventral view of thorax of eastern Palaearctic and Oriental Megasternini. A. Bolbonotum sp. B. Kahanga inconspicua, holotype. C. Australocyon sp. (A. pilocnemoides group). D. Nipponocercyon shibatai. E. Cycreon floricola. F. Pilocnema sp." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/408733" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.50078.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Morphology of Himalcercyon franzi sp. nov. A. Mentum. B. Prosternum and hypomeron. C. Mesoventral elevation. D. Antenna. E. Mesotarsus, ventral view. F. Median portion of metaventrite. G. Elytral punctation. H. Elytral apex." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/408729" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

